radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. A 1.1 cm left hepatic hypodensity likely represents a cyst or hepatic hemangioma. Several smaller hepatic hypodensities likely represent cysts. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 1.3 cm, containing numerous intraluminal appendicoliths and surrounding inflammatory change. Trace fluid is noted along the right pericolic gutter. No evidence of perforation or associated abscess formation. Small umbilical hernia containing fat noted.
